title: Matchsafe, ""The Sportsman" magazine", 1899–1900
provenance: Collection of Carol B. Brener and Stephen W. Brener
description: Rectangular, rounded corners and sides, featuring polychrome enamel decoration of kangaroo holding cricket bat with seated lion in background, inscribed above animals "The Sportsman" and below "for Cricket News". Reverse features very worn inscription "SEP 1899". Lid hinged on upper left. Striker on bottom.
creditline: Gift of Stephen W. Brener and Carol B. Brener
markings: W.N, lion passant, Chester town mark, date letter "Q" all stamped on bezel; "T" stamped on reverse bezel; worn lion passant stamp on lid front.
